1. KiloEx: The vulnerability has been fixed and a compensation plan is being formulated. A case has been filed in Hong Kong;
2. Stellar: Plans to put $3 billion of real-world assets on the chain by the end of 2025;
3. Market news: Binance has approached multiple sovereign wealth funds to establish cryptocurrency reserves;
4. US SEC: Crypto asset market maker CLS Global FZC has admitted to violating securities laws;
5. Circle launches Refund Protocol, a non-custodial dispute resolution solution for stablecoin payments;
6. VanEck launches NODE, an exchange-traded fund that tracks cryptocurrency stocks;
7. Blockworks Research: Hyperliquid's average daily trading volume has reached $6.4 billion in the past three months;
8. Zero Edge founder Richard Kim was arrested for misappropriating investor funds for gambling;
9. DCG founder: When BTC was discovered, the price was only $7-8, and investing in BTC is more profitable than investing in crypto startups;
10. In March, Google search keywords Bitcoin and Ethereum have rebounded, reaching the highest level of the year;
11. Justin Sun: Ethereum price is low, no intention to sell;
12. In the past 7 days, Solana DEX transaction volume exceeded 16 billion US dollars, ranking first.
